Windows commands:

The Batch file(.bat) file is a script file in windows, The commands executes in cmd are listed in file save with .bat extetion.
It will execute all series of commands quickly

echo commands:
    echo Raghu > C:\windows\Users\nraghu\raghu.txt  --> create the raghu.txt with Raghu content
    
    echo %ENV_VARIABLE%  --> printing the value of env variable
         ex: echo %HOMEDRIVE%, echo %HOMEPATH%, echo %username%
         
xcopy and copy command:

if and else in bat file:

set command:
     set name="Raghu M N"  --> setting the env variable, valid till the that cmd open 
     
   

